{"name": "Core Lep'ix", "type": "race", "img": "icons/environment/creatures/bug-tick-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Lep'ix are bipedal, insectoid vertebrates with a smooth, generally grey, exoskeleton. Though they are shorter on average than humans and chk'tu, their frame is generally more lithe and their figure is accented by the presence of large butterfly or moth-like wings. Lep'ix also possess a single pair of large, round eyes as well as a pair of bent, fern-like antennae. Often, they will also have a thick mane of filaments resembling fur around the neck, trailing off to a less thick covering along the head and shoulders.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The wings of no two Lep'ix are alike in shape or pattern, and some communities of Lep'ix are imbued with various forms of otherworldly magic which further differentiates the kinds of mesmerizing patterns that can be found upon them.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "portion": "core", "classDetails": "<p>Core Lep'ix Traits</p><ul><li><b>Compatibility: </b>Insectoid</li><li><b>Attribute Increase: </b>Your Presence increases by 1.</li><li><b>Lifespan: </b>Lep'ix reach maturity around 5 years old and live to 50 or 60 years on average.</li><li><b>Size: </b>Medium; Lep'ix are generally between 4 to 5 feet tall, and weigh between 70 to 140 pounds.</li><li><b>Speed: </b>Your base ground speed is 30 feet.</li><li><b>Flutter Fall: </b>@Compendium[undertaking.abilities.XQVA2ZE3HFJHJ8Z4]{Flutter Fall}</li><li><b>Captivating Patterns:</b> Your wings are a tapestry of mesmerizing patterns. You know the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.S19PI54SQR9C8R14]{Captivate} cantrip. Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence is your spellcasting attribute for it (chosen when you select this race).</b></li><li><b>Delicate Wings: </b>Your Constitution score decreases by 1. If your branch race grants you the Flutter Fall ability again or a flying speed, ignore this penalty.</li><li><b>Weak Build: </b>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.5FAD194X1HDZFU2U]{Weak Build}</li><li><b>Insectoid Creature: </b>@Compendium[undertaking.abilities.2ZY5QMOZSWWLGX2V]{Insectoid Creature}</li><li><b>Languages: </b>You can speak, read, and write Common and Chitter.</li></ul>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "ZXRXCHIPV04IUNZ2", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Core Mandrid", "type": "race", "img": "icons/creatures/fish/fish-shark-swimming.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Mandrids are bipedal humanoids that, strangely enough, resemble any one of a variety of salamanders walking upright. They are slightly shorter and stockier on average than humans, and they have a tail that extends behind them by roughly their height. Like salamanders, they are fully amphibious and dwell on land as often as beneath the water. Their skin is smooth and perpetually moist to the touch, save for when they are extremely dehydrated.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "portion": "core", "classDetails": "<p>Core Mandrid Traits</p><ul><li><b>Compatibility: </b>Aquatic</li><li><b>Attribute Increase: </b>Your Constitution and Presence scores both increase by 1.</li><li><b>Lifespan: </b>Mandrids reach maturity around 20 years old and live 150 to 200 years on average.</li><li><b>Size: </b>Medium; Mandrid height is generally between 4 1/2 to 6 feet tall, and they weigh between 100 and 200 pounds.</li><li><b>Speed: </b>Your base walking speed is 30 feet.</li><li><b>Natural Swimmer: </b>You have a swim speed of 30 feet.</li><li><b>Amphibious: </b>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.FIAKA97FYXBI8RXA]{Amphibious}</li><li><b>Moist Skin: </b>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.OQYT9KI73HD5VRJI]{Moist Skin}</li><li><b>Languages: </b>You can speak, read, and write Common and Aquan.</li></ul>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "LFRU13U7JVI9NQ3Y", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Core Minotaur", "type": "race", "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/paw-print-tan.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Minotaurs are bipedal beings reminiscent of humans, though unlike humans they have a head resembling a bull's, hooved feet, and a covering of short, bovine fur. Minotaur fur generally comes in shades of brown, white, black, or a mixture of those colors. Regardless of whether they are male or female, the head of a minotaur is adorned with a formidable pair of bull-like horns. Their bodies also tend to have a larger build than humans, with the average minotaur sharing a height with some of the tallest humans.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "portion": "core", "classDetails": "<p>Core Minotaur Traits</p><ul><li><b>Compatibility: </b>Bestial</li><li><b>Attribute Increase: </b>Your Strength and Constitution scores both increase by 1.</li><li><b>Lifespan: </b>Minotaurs reach adulthood in their mid-teens and few live past 80 years of age.</li><li><b>Size: </b>Medium; Minotaur height generally ranges from 5 and a half to 7 feet tall, and their weight ranges from below 150 lbs. to 275 lbs. or more.</li><li><b>Speed: </b>Your base walking speed is 30 feet.</li><li><b>Horns: </b>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.KE1XK9SLI0D93UHX]{Horns (Minotaur)}</li><li><b>Bull Rush: </b>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.LGWWYVXE4UCUIR9I]{Bull Rush}</li><li><b>Trailblazer: </b>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.HL7IFX1LMPKKB7LJ]{Trailblazer}</li><li><b>Bestial Creature: </b>@Compendium[undertaking.abilities.A69S7OIOQPX7A5GA]{Bestial Creature}</li><li><b>Languages: </b>You can speak, read, and write Common and Landspeak.</li></ul>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "K5ER3882YONF2SAT", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
